[[File:AnnaGabriellaCeccatelli1990s.jpg|thumb|160px]] '''Anna Gabriella Ceccatelli''', known as '''Gabriella''' (1 December 1927 – 21 February 2001), was an Italian politician. Ceccatelli was born in [[Prato]], Florence.<ref name=senato1/> She was the undersecretary of the [[Ministry of the Environment (Italy)|environmental ministry]] in the [[Giovanni Goria]]<ref>[https://storia.camera.it/governi/i-governo-goria/Ministero%20dell'ambiente I Governo Goria] {{it icon}}</ref> and [[Ciriaco De Mita|De Mita]]<ref>[https://storia.camera.it/governi/i-governo-de-mita/Ministero%20dell'ambiente I Governo De Mita] {{it icon}}</ref> governments, and very close to Catholic associations.<ref>[https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1994/05/25/famiglia-cristiana-attacca-cl.html ' FAMIGLIA CRISTIANA' ATTACCA CL] {{it icon}}</ref> Ceccatelli was also a [[Senate of Italy|Senator]] between 1983 and 1992 for the [[Christian Democracy (Italy)|Christian Democracy]] party.<ref name=senato1>[http://www.senato.it/leg/09/BGT/Schede/Attsen/00000550.htm Anna Gabriella CECCATELLI] {{it icon}}</ref><ref>[http://www.senato.it/leg/10/BGT/Schede/Attsen/00000550.htm Anna Gabriella CECCATELLI] {{it icon}}</ref>
