{{Infobox person | name = Jamisha Gilbert | image = | caption = | image_size = | birth_place = [[Baltimore]], Maryland, U.S. | birth_date = March 29, 1995 | death_date = {{Death date and age|2013|12|04|1995|03|29}} | death_place = [[Lynchburg, Virginia]], U.S. | death_cause = [[Hypothermia]] | occupation = | notable_works = }} '''Jamisha Monique Gilbert''' (March 29, 1995 - December 4, 2013) was an American [[YouTube]] personality and aspiring [[lawyer]] who mysteriously died on December 4, 2013 after smoking marijuana.<ref>http://www.newsadvance.com/news/local/jamisha-gilbert-s-death-explained-but-questions-remain/article_d9b08bdc-cbbb-11e3-a07d-0017a43b2370.html</ref><ref>http://www.whsv.com/home/headlines/Investigators-Jamisha-Gilbert-Died-of-Hypothermia-No-Charges-Will-Be-Filed-256605501.html</ref>
==Education== Jamisha graduated from [[Heritage High School (Lynchburg, Virginia)|Heritage High School]] in 2013. She had plans to go to [[The University of Maryland]] to study law.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wdbj7.com/news/local/jamisha-gilberts-death-is-not-the-first-tragedy-her-family-has-faced/23342476 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-01-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305180324/http://www.wdbj7.com/news/local/jamisha-gilberts-death-is-not-the-first-tragedy-her-family-has-faced/23342476 |archivedate=2016-03-05 |df= }}</ref><ref>http://wtvr.com/2013/12/05/medical-examiner-positively-ids-body-as-missing-teen/</ref>
==Disappearance and death== Gilbert was found dead in a briar patch near Megginson Cemetery on December fourth. Crews, who scoured the area for days after she disappeared, used chainsaws to reach her body in the heavily wooded area.<ref>http://www.roanoke.com/news/virginia/jamisha-gilbert-s-death-attributed-to-hypothermia/article_9ae63ab4-cc24-11e3-a141-0017a43b2370.html</ref> She was naked when discovered, yet there was no evidence of sexual assault.<ref>http://wset.com/archive/local-doctor-weighs-in-on-jamisha-gilberts-toxicology-report</ref> She had small amounts of marijuana in her system; the drug likely contributed to death, although the degree to which marijuana contributed to death is uncertain. She was covered in scratches, most likely from a car accident which happened moments prior to her death, in which her car crashed into a guardrail at the intersection of Concord Turnpike and Winston Ridge Road.<ref>http://newsone.com/2798515/jamisha-gilbert-missing-virginia/</ref><ref>http://www.newsplex.com/home/headlines/Police-Body-Found-in-Lynchburg-is-Jamisha-Gilbert-234612501.html</ref><ref>http://www.theglobaldispatch.com/jamisha-gilbert-identified-as-virginia-woman-found-dead-police-investigation-ongoing-97055/</ref> The main cause of death was listed as hypothermia.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wdbj7.com/news/local/lynchburg-commonwealths-attorney-to-hold-news-conference-about-jamisha-gilberts-death/25637666 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-01-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819113449/http://www.wdbj7.com/news/local/lynchburg-commonwealths-attorney-to-hold-news-conference-about-jamisha-gilberts-death/25637666 |archivedate=2014-08-19 |df= }}</ref>
