The '''Lion of Gripsholm Castle''' is a notable example of bad taxidermy, in the museum of [[Gripsholm Castle]], in [[Sweden]]. The lion is badly stuffed; it has a comically unrealistic face.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hilariously Bad Lion Taxidermy|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/donnad/hilariously-bad-lion-taxidermy|publisher=Buzzfeed|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref>
==History== In 1731, the Bey of Algiers presented King [[Frederick I of Sweden]] with a lion. It was one of the first lions in Scandinavia.<ref>{{cite web|title=Le lion empaillé de Gripsholm|url=http://www.laboiteverte.fr/le-lion-empaille-de-gripsholm/|work=La Boite Verte|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref> When alive, the lion was kept in a cage near [[Junibacken]]. When the lion died, it was stuffed and mounted, but the taxidermist and the museum-keepers would have been unfamiliar with the appearance of live lions.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Greatest Castles in Sweden: Uncovering Magical Swedish Castles|url=http://www.exploring-castles.com/castles_in_sweden.html#gripsholm_lion|work=Exploring Castles|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref> However, from the side, the setting does resemble a heraldic lion rather than a "real" lion.
==Notoriety== In the 21st century, the badly-stuffed lion has been widely mocked.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bad taxidermy: The lion at the castle of Gripsholm |url=http://www.doobybrain.com/2011/08/17/bad-taxidermy-the-lion-at-the-castle-of-gripsholm/ |publisher=Doobybrain |accessdate=9 March 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140309201041/http://www.doobybrain.com/2011/08/17/bad-taxidermy-the-lion-at-the-castle-of-gripsholm/ |archivedate= 9 March 2014 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The lion of Gripsholm's castle|url=http://www.ulrikagood.com/2011/04/lion-of-gripshoms-castle.html|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The stuffed lion of Gripsholm’s Castle|url=http://www.eversostrange.com/2011/03/27/the-stuffed-lion-of-gripsholms-castle/|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=18th Century Taxidermy Unkind to Noble Lion|url=http://www.geekosystem.com/lion-taxidermy/|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Lion of Gripsholm Castle|url=http://mentalfloss.com/article/27487/lion-gripsholm-castle|publisher=Mentalfloss|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lejonet på Gripsholms Slott|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/Lejonet-p%C3%A5-Gripsholms-Slott/113607498385|work=Facebook|accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref>
